        "id": 1691662,
        "name": "Nick Gangas",
        "username": "Nick_Gangas",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/n/ecd19e/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2015-06-21T01:56:54.000Z",
        "cooked": "<ul>\n<li>\n<a href=\"http://www.cellartracker.com/note.asp?iWine=1778975&amp;iNote=5063873\"><strong>2012 Georges Noellat Vosne-Roman\u00e9e 1er Cru Les Beaux Monts</strong></a> <em>- France, Burgundy, C\u00f4te de Nuits, Vosne-Roman\u00e9e 1er Cru (6/20/2015)</em><br>\nFirst impression was a big whiff of wood. Wine was medium bodied, red fruit and a little minerality. Avg. finish. Next night the wood was still there the wine had evolved some but not for the better. The fruit was not typical of the vintage. Not well balanced. Ok experience. If someone popped a bottle I would drink a glass but not seek this out. Way overpriced and hyped. Not typical of other 2012\u2019s.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Posted from <a href=\"http://www.cellartracker.com/\">CellarTracker</a></em></p>",
